          </table>
        </div>
        <p>
          An IV can safely deliver <b>part</b> of this volume quickly (e.g., ~1.0–1.2&nbsp;L as
          clinically appropriate), and the rest can be taken orally—restoring plasma volume fast
          without overloading the gut.
        </p>

